com.i2group.apollo.events.transport

Interface IItemChangeSet

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IChangeSet<CardChangeSet,CardChangeSet>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IItemChangeSetCommand
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AddCardToItem, AmendCardOnItem, CardAddedToItemEvent, CardAmendedEvent, CardDeletedFromItemEvent, CreateEntity, CreateLink, DeleteCardFromItem, EntityCreatedEvent, EntityMergedEvent, LinkCreatedEvent

    public interface IItemChangeSet
extends IChangeSet<CardChangeSet,CardChangeSet>
    A set of changes made to an Item by executing a command.

    Items in the Analysis Repository are created, populated, and maintained by sequences of commands. These commands do not require data in the form of entities, links, and properties. Instead, the commands need data in card change sets that describe changes to the contents of new or existing cards.

    Note: Although they have superficially similar names, there is no connection between a set and a change set.

    A single card change set describes the changes to be made to a single card in the Analysis Repository. This design has two consequences:

    • The commands that create items in the repository require zero or more card change sets, containing properties and property groups for each new item. Supplying more than one card change set results in the creation of more than one card.
    • The commands that edit an item in the repository require exactly one card change set. This change set contains information about changes to the properties and property groups on a single card. Changing more than one card therefore requires more than one command.
        • For example, to create an entity with two cards, use a single command that contains two card change sets. To add two new cards to an existing entity, use two commands with one card change set in each.
    Since:
    1.0
